    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 16th prioritizing ceiling in the middle-order, headlined by **Yordan Alvarez** (65.44) as our premier start. Facing J.C. Mejia, **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a strong platoon advantage and a premium #2 spot in the order, driving his efficiency well into our \"Strong\" tier. While **Junior Caminero** (59.77) narrowly misses that threshold, he remains a high-floor play despite a challenging matchup against Leasure; his spot in the lineup coupled with a +4% adjustment for the R/R dynamic platoon makes him nearly indispensable. **Gary Sanchez** (58.68) also provides significant value today; the matchup against the struggling Corbin provides enough of a lift to nearly reach the 60-point \"Strong\" threshold, making him the most viable utility option currently on the active roster.\n\nOn the periphery of the lineup, the decision-making process was tight, particularly regarding **Josh Smith** (39.60). Although **Josh Smith** carried some intrigue due to park factors, his negative adjustment for batting eighth and a unfavorable platoon split against Lopez pushed him just below the Zebras' 40-point floor. Protecting our game caps remains paramount, so we will keep **Josh Smith** on the bench in favor of more efficient platoon configurations. We are also monitoring **Dillon Dingler** (55.99) closely; his matchup against Bubic is aided by a massive +14% platoon boost, though we are keeping an eye on the 40% SB hold rate of the opposing staff, which limits his base-stealing upside. **Kazuma Okamoto** (52.14) rounds out the infield, acting as a stable, if unspectacular, option against Sproat. With **Christian Yelich** remaining sidelined on the IL, our depth is currently tested, and we will continue to rely on the underlying projections to navigate these daily marginal start decisions.",
